President Obama met with a group of western Governors to discuss issues such as drought, wildfire, and extreme weather events. He reiterated the Administration's commitment to aid preparedness, response, and recovery from natural disasters. The President proposed a new approach in his upcoming budget to fund wildfire suppression more effectively. The meeting also addressed the impact of climate change on extreme weather and the progress made on the Climate Action Plan. The President expressed his desire to continue working with Governors to address these issues for the benefit of future generations. Several Governors and Administration Officials participated in the meeting.